<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870901-0113 </DOCNO><HL> Dividend News:Neiman-Marcus Group Inc.</HL><DD> 09/01/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> DIVIDENDS (DIV) </IN><TEXT>   NEIMAN-MARCUS GROUP INC. declared an initial quarterly cash dividend of five cents a share, payable Oct. 30 to stock of record Oct. 9. The Newton, Mass.-based specialty retailer, which was recently spun off by Carter Hawley Hale Stores Inc., said directors &quot;adopted a modest dividend payout policy, in view of the company's earnings outlook for the fiscal year ending July 31, 1988, and the capital requirements relating to its extensive store renovation and expansion program.&quot; </TEXT></DOC>